Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
3.3  Why rotation forces columns \[Dash] a one-line scaling argument\
\>", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"001c0f27-8648-4695-9650-3c48e970d3c7"],

Cell["\<\
The Taylor\[Dash]Proudman result can be read as a scaling statement. Vertical \
variations of the flow are suppressed by a factor of the Rossby number: a \
structure of horizontal scale L develops vertical variation only over a \
height \[TildeTilde] L / Ro. When Ro \[LessLess] 1 that height exceeds the \
domain, so the structure spans it as a column. Rapidly rotating convection is \
therefore generically columnar in three dimensions. This explains why 3-D \
convection looks the way it does \[Dash] but it is a statement about vertical \
(axis-parallel) structure, which the 2-D barotropic model does not represent. \
The simulation does NOT reproduce banana cells.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"16302a77-7cd8-4de1-a1bd-d1b0d6655905"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["4.  The Numerical Method", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"11bfacc5-f002-4e35-b7d8-73ab35ec9f2e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The solver is spectral: it represents \[Omega] by its spherical-harmonic \
coefficients ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubsuperscriptBox["\[Omega]", "l", "m"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c5de4816-2082-4c71-9c5f-f1001f69db15"],
 " and steps those coefficients forward in time. Two properties of spherical \
harmonics make this the natural choice on a sphere."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bd33b582-8546-4429-b275-6997d9659ab8"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["4.1  Spherical harmonics diagonalise the Laplacian", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"ba4b5c8c-02fd-4be7-8742-ead3a24d89c0"],

Cell["\<\
The single most useful fact for the whole method: spherical harmonics are \
eigenfunctions of the horizontal Laplacian, with eigenvalue -l(l+1) (on the \
unit sphere):\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9a86593b-491d-41b5-95ce-cf37ac2569aa"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"], 
    SubsuperscriptBox["Y", "l", "m"]}], "=", 
   RowBox[{"-", "l", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"l", "+", "1"}], ")"}], " ", 
    SubsuperscriptBox["Y", "l", "m"]}]}], TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",\

 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"750f30cb-ba61-41df-b5bd-9c3d7245c527"],

Cell["\<\
Differential operators become multiplication by numbers. Inverting the \
Laplacian to get the streamfunction from the vorticity \[Dash] a global \
Poisson solve \[Dash] is then a single division per mode:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"62bd226b-64b5-4f14-8389-2cac4c0e1921"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[Psi]", "l", "m"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"-", "1"}], 
     RowBox[{"l", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"l", "+", "1"}], ")"}]}]], " ", 
    SubsuperscriptBox["\[Omega]", "l", "m"]}]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"7990752a-7f38-48f7-a476-982a713948af"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is the array _inv_ev in simulate_v6.py. The l = 0 mode is set to zero \
(a constant streamfunction carries no flow). Let us verify the eigenvalue \
property symbolically \[Dash] apply the angular (Laplace\[Dash]Beltrami) \
operator to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubsuperscriptBox["Y", "l", "m"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cde43039-643d-4bb2-a531-f662f7796166"],
 " and divide it back out:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ca0e98ad-d6db-4645-bb62-dd1dea9c4d64"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
angularLaplacian[f_, \[Theta]_, \[Phi]_] :=
  1/Sin[\[Theta]] D[Sin[\[Theta]] D[f, \[Theta]], \[Theta]] + \
1/Sin[\[Theta]]^2 D[f, {\[Phi], 2}];

Table[
  Simplify[
   angularLaplacian[SphericalHarmonicY[l, m, \[Theta], \[Phi]], \[Theta], \
\[Phi]] /
    SphericalHarmonicY[l, m, \[Theta], \[Phi]]],
  {l, 0, 4}, {m, 0, 0}]
(* returns {0, -2, -6, -12, -20} = -l(l+1) *)\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[8]:=",ExpressionUUID->"e25cc7be-cd17-4d93-8dab-ee1a9ab0fe22"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0", "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"-", "2"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"-", "6"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"-", "12"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"-", "20"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.992517340137403*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[10]=",ExpressionUUID->"370b158f-6f31-4dcc-b244-8b23b313b871"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
The output {0, -2, -6, -12, -20} is exactly -l(l+1) for l = 0\[Ellipsis]4. \
The eigenvalue depends only on l, never on m \[Dash] all 2l+1 harmonics of a \
given degree share the same scale.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2db1c379-5b61-4b7b-bc7a-877b40f50850"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "4.2  Hyperviscosity: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "8"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "49864719-02a3-428f-b320-a3f164d013f9"],
 " instead of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3fb172ff-e3ff-41a7-bc3f-7d1373cca55e"]
}], "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"f92ca7b6-7232-4c81-9985-bf527236692a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A real fluid dissipates through ordinary viscosity, \[Nu]",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "db1880c7-7106-4087-bb76-00d760d2ae8e"],
 "\[Omega], whose spectral damping rate scales as l(l+1). But at the Sun's \
Ekman number a faithful \[Nu] would be so tiny that the smallest resolved \
scales, unable to dissipate, would pile up enstrophy and blow up the run. The \
fix is hyperviscosity: replace ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "737d5d29-f9e2-495b-acfd-95906ac052fd"],
 " with a higher power. This solver uses ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "8"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9b3ea13a-eb19-48d7-a9db-9c0509010fd6"],
 ", whose damping rate scales as [l(l+1)",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["]", "4"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7dd558e2-6536-4cb1-8161-bc55f0ea1e04"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5ec3052f-8765-4135-8b00-68b674088c79"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"damping", " ", "rate"}], 
    RowBox[{"(", "l", ")"}]}], "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "+", "\[Nu]", " ", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"l", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"l", "+", "1"}], ")"}]}], ")"}], "4"]}]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"41adb5d0-2b62-490c-818f-f8365089fd81"],

Cell["\<\
The key difference is selectivity. Because the exponent is so high, \
hyperviscosity is essentially inert across the whole inertial range and then \
switches on abruptly near the truncation wavenumber, cleanly absorbing the \
enstrophy that cascades to the grid scale while leaving the physically \
meaningful large and intermediate scales almost untouched. The plot compares \
the two, both normalised to bite at the same rate at l = 127:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"469cf18d-acd1-4ff7-8988-557e22f73db7"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"With", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"lmax", "=", "127"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"mu", "=", "0.03"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"nu", "=", "6.*^-17"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"dt", "=", "0.0015"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"Module", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"lam", ",", "hyper", ",", "ord", ",", "nuOrd"}], "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"lam", "[", "l_", "]"}], ":=", 
       RowBox[{"l", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"l", "+", "1"}], ")"}]}]}], ";", 
      RowBox[{"nuOrd", "=", 
       RowBox[{"nu", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"lam", "[", "lmax", "]"}], "^", "4"}], "/", 
         RowBox[{"lam", "[", "lmax", "]"}]}]}]}], ";", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"hyper", "[", "l_", "]"}], ":=", 
       RowBox[{"nu", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"lam", "[", "l", "]"}], "^", "4"}]}]}], ";", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"ord", "[", "l_", "]"}], ":=", 
       RowBox[{"nuOrd", 
        RowBox[{"lam", "[", "l", "]"}]}]}], ";", 
      RowBox[{"LogPlot", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"ord", "[", "l", "]"}], ",", 
          RowBox[{"hyper", "[", "l", "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"l", ",", "1", ",", "lmax"}], "}"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"PlotRange", "->", "All"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"PlotPoints", "->", "200"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"PlotStyle", "->", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"Gray", ",", "Dashed"}], "}"}], ",", 
           RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"RGBColor", "[", 
              RowBox[{"0.8", ",", "0.1", ",", "0.1"}], "]"}], ",", "Thick"}], 
            "}"}]}], "}"}]}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"PlotLegends", "->", 
         RowBox[{"Placed", "[", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"{", 
            
            RowBox[{"\"\<ordinary \[Nu]\!\(\*SuperscriptBox[\(\[Del]\), \
\(2\)]\)  (rate \[Proportional] l(l+1))\>\"", 
             ",", "\"\<hyperviscosity \[Nu]\!\(\*SuperscriptBox[\(\[Del]\), \
\(8\)]\)  (rate \[Proportional] [l(l+1)\!\(\*SuperscriptBox[\(]\), \
\(4\)]\))\>\""}], "}"}], ",", "Below"}], "]"}]}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"Frame", "->", "True"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"GridLines", "->", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"60", ",", "80"}], "}"}], ",", "None"}], "}"}]}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"FrameLabel", "->", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          
          RowBox[{"\"\<spherical-harmonic degree l\>\"", 
           ",", "\"\<dissipation rate\>\""}], "}"}]}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"ImageSize", "->", "440"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"PlotLabel", "->", 
         RowBox[{"Style", "[", 
          
          RowBox[{"\"\<Scale-selective dissipation\>\"", ",", "13", ",", 
           "Bold"}], "]"}]}]}], "]"}]}]}], "]"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[12]:=",ExpressionUUID->"f15a409f-94ae-4d83-8845-bc292e599a4f"],

