Cell[TextData[{
 "HONESTY, as flagged in the v6 audit (\[Section]4.4): the exact ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"r", "/", "R"}], ")"}], "l"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6d98c0a6-7d68-4fe2-8ba1-a45d41bf6b38"],
 " above puts a forcing-scale mode (l \[TildeTilde] 70) at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["0.71", "70"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e29efb46-60cf-4a5a-b7de-643f5e72a953"],
 " \[TildeTilde] 4\[Times]",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["10", 
   RowBox[{"-", "11"}]]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9c4cc735-6c8c-49c8-9d9a-6c2633461aa9"],
 " of its surface amplitude at the base \[Dash] i.e. the deep interior is \
essentially empty of small-scale structure. To fill the cutaway for display, \
the actual renderer (visualize_v6.py) softens the decay to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"r", "/", "R"}], ")"}], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"l", "/", 
     SubscriptBox["L", "ref"]}], ")"}]]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0f39ce57-fbaf-496c-9c7a-2abe30c936c1"],
 " with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["L", "ref"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0d34a05e-f0dd-441d-a31a-77537360c0ef"],
 " \[TildeTilde] 10, which OVERSTATES the penetration of forcing-scale modes \
by ~10\[Times] (painting l \[TildeTilde] 70 at ~9% at the base). That is an \
illustrative choice to avoid an almost-blank interior, honestly labelled as \
such \[Dash] a 2-D barotropic model carries no radial structure at all."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"570f5ece-9f0e-4504-8b59-28a12714b78f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "An equatorial cross-section makes the effect concrete. Taking a single \
longitudinal wave cos(6\[Lambda]) (a stand-in for one l = 6 surface mode) and \
multiplying by its regular-solid-harmonic weight ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"r", "/", "R"}], ")"}], "6"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "00517c23-3194-41e2-89f0-ccf5c93e3fcb"],
 " gives structure that is strong near the rim and decays smoothly inward \
\[Dash] shell-following, not vertical columns. A 2-D surface field simply has \
no mechanism to make Taylor columns:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"07cee778-db19-477e-a902-15d0f9a3ecc4"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Module[{rIn = 0.71, rOut = 1.0, w, field},
 w[r_] := (r/rOut)^6;
 field[r_, \[Lambda]_] := w[r] Cos[6 \[Lambda]];
 DensityPlot[field[Sqrt[x^2 + y^2], ArcTan[x, y]],
  {x, 0, rOut}, {y, 0, rOut},
  RegionFunction -> Function[{x, y}, rIn <= Sqrt[x^2 + y^2] <= rOut],
  ColorFunction -> (ColorData[\"TemperatureMap\"][Rescale[#, {-1, 1}]] &),
  ColorFunctionScaling -> False, PlotPoints -> 90, Mesh -> None,
  Frame -> True, AspectRatio -> 1, ImageSize -> 360,
  PlotLabel -> Style[\"Equatorial cut: (r/R)^l reconstruction\", 13, Bold]]]\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[17]:=",ExpressionUUID->"824bc962-fa80-43a8-aaa4-2127e75cca4f"],

