Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["6.  Results and Discussion", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"28946fd5-3203-4454-8ab2-f549049201c8"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["6.1  What the simulation shows", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"88d272f1-ed5c-4387-b0ff-54afd4852ef6"],

Cell["\<\
Run at high rotation (\[CapitalOmega] = 40, spectral truncation T127) and \
spun up for ~5 drag times, the model settles into a statistically steady, \
rotation-dominated turbulent state. The characteristic features \[Dash] and, \
honestly, the features it was hoped for but does NOT show:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"dfcf85d2-a4c4-4511-b190-1ebcaf1e024f"],

Cell["\<\
A broad, filamentary vorticity field. The spectrum genuinely broadened \
relative to v5 \[Dash] roughly 53% of the enstrophy below / 31% in / 16% \
above the forcing band, versus v5's 97% trapped in-band \[Dash] so a forward \
enstrophy cascade and some inverse transfer both exist. This is the real, \
measurable v6 improvement.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5b83ab75-6bda-48c6-93ca-cade0d75331c"],

Cell["\<\
A broad inertial range of thin vorticity filaments, sustained by the weak, \
scale-selective hyperviscosity that only bites near the truncation.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"13599e92-23e3-41c8-aa88-f786a0798c66"],

Cell["\<\
A statistically steady balance: stochastic forcing injects at l = \
60\[Dash]80, the forward enstrophy cascade drains to small scales, and linear \
drag removes large-scale energy. (A caveat quantified in the audit: ~42% of \
the injected energy is lost to hyperviscosity at small scales rather than \
cascading upscale, because the forcing sits close to the dissipation range.)\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"acd8d509-373b-4344-8395-c1ac6c769162"],

Cell["\<\
NO zonal jets. The \[Beta]-effect imposes some equator\[Dash]pole anisotropy \
and Rossby-wave activity, but zonal (m = 0) energy is only ~3.7% \[Dash] \
essentially isotropic turbulence with a whisper of anisotropy, NOT a jet \
regime (which would be 50\[Dash]90% zonal). The scale separation that would \
drive jets is marginal (Rhines degree l_R \[TildeTilde] 23 vs forcing 60\
\[Dash]80), so the advertised \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]jets from an arrested \
inverse cascade\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] are NOT achieved at these parameters. \
The legitimate niche of this class of model is Jupiter-like 2-D geostrophic \
turbulence, which this particular run does not reach.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5e08b2e2-1adb-4aec-859f-83a89072ba33"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["6.2  How it compares to full 3-D convection codes", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"cb687d0f-9392-4ecb-a283-36e76964fce9"],

Cell["\<\
Global solar-convection models such as ASH (Anelastic Spherical Harmonic; \
Brun & Toomre 2002) and Rayleigh (Featherstone & Hindman 2016) solve the full \
three-dimensional anelastic equations \[Dash] momentum, energy, and often \
induction \[Dash] on a radially resolved spherical shell. Relative to those, \
the barotropic model is a deliberate, extreme simplification.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"44ed4b51-783b-4957-8161-ad2f3f25a574"],

Cell["\<\
The table summarises what the barotropic model keeps and what it discards.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"daaca87b-c665-4783-9085-6f2aa52056bc"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Grid[{
  {Style[\"Feature\", Bold], Style[\"Barotropic (this model)\", Bold], Style[\
\"3-D anelastic (ASH / Rayleigh)\", Bold]},
  {\"Spatial dimensions\", \"2-D (one spherical surface)\", \"3-D (radially \
resolved shell)\"},
  {\"Prognostic fields\", \"vorticity \[Omega] only\", \"velocity, entropy, \
(magnetic field)\"},
  {\"Rotation / Coriolis\", \"yes (f = 2\[CapitalOmega] sin\[Phi])\", \"yes \
(full Coriolis)\"},
  {\"Buoyancy driving\", \"none (imposed stochastic stirring)\", \"genuine \
thermal buoyancy\"},
  {\"Radial structure\", \"none (reconstructed for display)\", \"resolved\"},
  {\"Differential rotation\", \"not captured\", \"emergent\"},
  {\"Magnetism / dynamo\", \"none\", \"optional (MHD)\"},
  {\"Cost\", \"seconds on a laptop\", \"CPU/GPU-hours on a cluster\"}
  },
 Frame -> All, Background -> {None, {LightYellow, None}},
 Alignment -> Left, Spacings -> {1.2, 1}, ItemSize -> {{12, 16, 18}, \
Automatic}]\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[19]:=",ExpressionUUID->"759808ed-df34-42a1-8942-8df55d09dc9a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[GridBox[{
    {
     StyleBox["\<\"Feature\"\>",
      StripOnInput->False,
      FontWeight->Bold], 
     StyleBox["\<\"Barotropic (this model)\"\>",
      StripOnInput->False,
      FontWeight->Bold], 
     StyleBox["\<\"3-D anelastic (ASH / Rayleigh)\"\>",
      StripOnInput->False,
      FontWeight->Bold]},
    {"\<\"Spatial dimensions\"\>", "\<\"2-D (one spherical surface)\"\>", "\<\
\"3-D (radially resolved shell)\"\>"},
    {"\<\"Prognostic fields\"\>", "\<\"vorticity \[Omega] only\"\>", \
"\<\"velocity, entropy, (magnetic field)\"\>"},
    {"\<\"Rotation / Coriolis\"\>", "\<\"yes (f = 2\[CapitalOmega] sin\[Phi])\
\"\>", "\<\"yes (full Coriolis)\"\>"},
    {"\<\"Buoyancy driving\"\>", "\<\"none (imposed stochastic \
stirring)\"\>", "\<\"genuine thermal buoyancy\"\>"},
    {"\<\"Radial structure\"\>", "\<\"none (reconstructed for display)\"\>", \
"\<\"resolved\"\>"},
    {"\<\"Differential rotation\"\>", "\<\"not captured\"\>", "\<\"emergent\"\
\>"},
    {"\<\"Magnetism / dynamo\"\>", "\<\"none\"\>", "\<\"optional (MHD)\"\>"},
    {"\<\"Cost\"\>", "\<\"seconds on a laptop\"\>", "\<\"CPU/GPU-hours on a \
cluster\"\>"}
   },
   AutoDelete->False,
   GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Left}}},
   GridBoxBackground->{"Columns" -> {{None}}, "Rows" -> {
       RGBColor[1, 1, 0.85], None}},
   GridBoxFrame->{"Columns" -> {{True}}, "Rows" -> {{True}}},
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {12, 16, 18}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}},
   GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {{1.2}}, "Rows" -> {{1}}}],
